# Security rules — Meavo org standard

Org standard (see STANDARDS.md §4 in meavo-agent-templates). Deviations for this repo are listed at the bottom.

## Auth at every layer

- Verify auth independently in: middleware (pages), section layouts, Server Actions, and API routes.
- Middleware passes `/api/*` through — never assume an API route is protected.
- This repo's auth gate: `getHolsUser()` / `requireHolsUser()` in `src/lib/access.ts` — call one of them at the top of every Server Action and API route.
- Tool card gating: check `ToolCardAccess` for `VACATION_TRACKER_CARD_ID` (`seed-vacation-tracker`, constant in `src/lib/vacation-tracker.ts`) at login AND on every authenticated request, so revocation in gateway Admin takes effect immediately. Never look up the card by `linkedAppKey` at runtime.

## Sessions & credentials

- NextAuth v5 JWT sessions; `systemRole` is refreshed from the DB in the session callback (`src/lib/auth.ts`).
- Passwords: bcryptjs 12 rounds, min 8 chars. Login throttling via shared `LoginThrottle` table (`src/lib/login-throttle.ts`, 10 failures / 15 min per email).
- Google OAuth is invite-only — user must already exist in the DB.

## Routes & rendering

- Cron routes: `CRON_SECRET` Bearer auth on every `/api/cron/*` handler.
- `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` on authenticated layouts and DB-touching pages.
- Never return stack traces to clients in production.

## Headers & content

- `next.config.ts` must set: `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`, `X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN`, `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin`, `Strict-Transport-Security`.
- Uploads: Vercel Blob, 10 MB limit, validate MIME + extension, stream downloads via authenticated route, sanitize filenames.
- Embedded HTML: sandboxed same-origin iframe with CSP `sandbox allow-scripts`.

## Secrets

- No secrets in client code, comments, or committed files.
- Document env var names in `.env.example` only — never values.

## Repo-specific deviations

- Tool-card ID is a hardcoded constant (`src/lib/vacation-tracker.ts`), not an env var like other satellites.
- Admins (`systemRole === "ADMIN"`) bypass the tool-card check in `getHolsUser()` — see STANDARDS.md §8 on admin-bypass inconsistency; do not extend this pattern.
- `X-Frame-Options` is `DENY` (stricter than the org's `SAMEORIGIN`).
- No file uploads or embedded HTML in this app — those rules are currently N/A.
- Session role fields are refreshed in the session callback rather than the JWT callback (same effect: fresh `systemRole` per request).
